%% Diagram: Persistence Flow Journal Checkpoint Recovery
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Browser Client
    participant MP as Multiplayer<br/>(Rust process)
    participant J as DynamoDB<br/>Journal (WAL)
    participant S as S3 Checkpoint
    participant R as Recovery /<br/>New Process

    Note over C,MP: Steady-state edit loop
    C->>MP: delta @ ~33ms
    MP->>MP: apply to in-memory state<br/>assign sequence #

    par Frequent journal write
        MP->>J: append delta<br/>(every ~0.5s)
        J-->>MP: ack (p95 ~600ms)
    and Infrequent checkpoint
        MP->>S: full snapshot<br/>(every 30-60s)
        S-->>MP: ack
    end

    Note over MP: Process crash
    MP-XR: lost in-memory state

    R->>S: load latest checkpoint
    S-->>R: snapshot @ seq=N
    R->>J: read journal entries<br/>where seq > N
    J-->>R: deltas N+1 ... M
    R->>R: replay → state @ seq=M

    Note over R,J: Worst-case data loss < 1s<br/>(vs 60s checkpoint-only)
